# forgeFit Bible Rule

Before writing or modifying forgeFit code:

1. Read `docs/BIBLE.md` — authoritative architecture, phases, features, design
2. Read `docs/PROGRESS.md` — current phase, last session, blockers, next steps
3. Read the active `docs/phases/NN-*.md` file for acceptance criteria

## Build Constraints

- Program logic lives in `program-engine` + `evidence-kb` only — never LLM-generated workouts
- Use Forge Ember tokens from `packages/ui` — no hardcoded hex colors
- Mobile-first at 375px; offline workout logging is mandatory (Phase 3+)
- One Supabase migration per logical schema change
- Follow `documentation-sync.mdc` after every change

## Phase Gate

Do not skip phases. Mark phase complete in `docs/PROGRESS.md` only when that phase's "done when" checklist passes.
